<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-10T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-10T12:00:00-05:00" n="223" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2394</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-10T18:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 10, 1916, 6 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 11, 8.15 a.
                                    m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>90. Department’s telegram 48,<note n="2" xml:id="d223fn2">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_159">p.
                                    159</ref>.</note> February 7. Am informed that no passengers on
                                boats sunk. Warning shot given, ships visited, papers taken, crews
                                given ten minutes to take to boats. Some other boats captured and
                                taken to port. Some chased and run aground.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_MIN1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>